    <h1 class="section-title" id="privacy-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="section-note"><strong>Last updated:</strong> January 2026</p>

    <p class="lead measure">
      This Privacy Policy explains how BrazilDecoded collects, uses, shares,
      and protects personal data when you use our website and forms.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Who we are (controller)</h2>
    <p>
      BrazilDecoded is the controller of personal data processed through this
      site. For inquiries, please contact us at
      <a href="mailto:contact@brazildecoded.com.br">contact@brazildecoded.com.br</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Data we collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Contact data:</strong> name, email address, and messages you submit.</li>
      <li><strong>Usage data:</strong> pages visited, clicks, referrer URL, and device/browser details.</li>
      <li><strong>Campaign data:</strong> UTM parameters and attribution tags.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. How we use your data</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Deliver requested resources (such as the starter kit) and respond to inquiries.</li>
      <li>Operate and improve the site, including analytics and troubleshooting.</li>
      <li>Measure marketing performance and campaign effectiveness.</li>
      <li>Prevent abuse, fraud, and security incidents.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Legal bases (LGPD)</h2>
    <p>We process personal data based on one or more of the following legal bases:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Consent:</strong> when you opt in or when required for cookies.</li>
      <li><strong>Contract:</strong> to provide content or services you request.</li>
      <li><strong>Legitimate interest:</strong> to improve the site and protect operations.</li>
      <li><strong>Legal obligation:</strong> to comply with applicable laws.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Data sharing</h2>
    <p>
      We do not sell personal data. We may share limited data with service
      providers that support hosting, analytics, automation, and form delivery.
      These providers process data only as necessary to provide services to us.
    </p>

    <h2>6. International transfers</h2>
    <p>
      Some service providers may process data outside Brazil. When required, we
      use appropriate safeguards to protect cross-border transfers.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Data retention</h2>
    <p>
      We keep personal data only as long as necessary for the purposes described
      here or to comply with legal obligations.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      You may request confirmation, access, correction, portability, deletion,
      anonymization, and withdrawal of consent, as applicable. To exercise your
      rights, please contact us at
      <a href="mailto:contact@brazildecoded.com.br">contact@brazildecoded.com.br</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Cookies</h2>
    <p>
      We use cookies to operate the site and, with your consent, for analytics
      and marketing. See the
      <a href="/cookies/">Cookie Consent Terms</a> for details.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Security</h2>
    <p>
      We use reasonable safeguards to protect personal data. No system is 100%
      secure, so please avoid sending sensitive data via forms.
    </p>

    <h2>11. Updates</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The latest version
      will always be available on this page.
    </p>
